II. It is something harsh to exclude the paschal supper out of the title τῆς ἑορτῆς τοῦ πάσχα, of the feast of the Pass- over, because the name of the whole feast takes its original from it. This they do who imagine this supper mentioned in this place to have been the0 paschal supper, and yet it was πρὸ τῆς ἑορτῆς τοῦ πάσχα, before the feast of the Passover.

We have therefore shewn‚ by many arguments in our notes upon Matt. xxvi.2‚6‚ that the supper here mentioned was the same with that at Bethany, in the house of ‘ Simon the leper,' two days before the Passover.
